<h2><a name="Tour highlights"></a><span class="geolocation-title">Tour highlights</span></h2>
<p>• Spend 7 nights on board a traditional Turkish yacht as it sails around the beautiful Aeolian Islands<br />• Visit each of the seven islands with free time in the evenings to soak up to atmosphere and enjoy dinner in local restaurants (payable locally)<br />• Enjoy a cosy private cabin on board with a private bathroom<br />• Lunch is included on board the boat with two courses and wine</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/tours-multi-centres/tours-multi-centres-in-italy/sailing-the-aeolian-islands#Tour highlights">[Back to top]</a></p>
<h2><a name="Itinerary"></a><span class="geolocation-title">Itinerary</span></h2>
<p><strong>Day 1: UK to Catania or Palermo</strong></p>
<p><span>On arrival at Catania Airport, you’ll be transferred to Milazzo Port where your boat awaits. Get ready to spend the next week cruising on the glorious Tyrrhenian Sea on this beautiful traditional Turkish yacht crafted in wood. Meet your skipper and enjoy a welcome drink before settling into your comfortable cabin. Tonight dinner will be served on board as you set sail towards Vulcano.</span></p>
<p>Meals included: Dinner</p>
<p><strong>Day 2: Vulcano</strong></p>
<p><span>Wake up to a view of the towering Vulcano, with its jagged rocks and steaming craters, surrounded by black volcanic sandy beaches. The active volcano dominates the land. The boat will stop in the harbour at Porto di Levante. The two main streets in the town offer you two options. One will lead you up to the crater trail and the other to the thermal waters of the sulfuric mud baths. Explore the island at your own pace before heading back to the boat.</span></p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast, Lunch</p>
<p><strong>Day 3: Lipari</strong></p>
<p><span>Today you’ll explore the largest of the Aeolian Islands, Liapri. The islands are famed for their dramatic coastlines and rugged rock formations called “faraglioni”. On today's boat trip around the island you’ll get to see these beautiful natural pale pumice rock formations from the best vantage point on the crystal clear water. You’ll be dropped off at the harbour to explore the old town. The castle that dominates the town is now home to the Aeolian Regional Archaeological Museum.</span></p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast, Lunch</p>
<p><strong>Day 4: Panarea</strong></p>
<p><span>Visit the smallest of the Aeolian Islands, Panarea. In the summer months you’ll see luxury yachts bobbing in the crystalline waters surrounding the fashionable island. A boat trip will take you around the island before dropping you at the port. Explore the pretty white washed pedestrianised village of San Pietro or relax in a secluded sandy cove for the afternoon.</span></p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast, Lunch</p>
<p><strong>Day 5: Stromboli</strong></p>
<p><span>Stromboli is another of the Aeolian Islands' three active volcanoes. Its conical silhouette rises from the sea. You’ll stop in the harbour where you can explore the islands main settlement and its black volcanic beaches. For those feeling active, it's possible to take guided walk up the blackened slopes of the Volcano to the crater(payable locally). This evening choose from one of island's restaurants to enjoy dinner (payable locally). After, immerse yourself in this incredibly unique setting as you take an excursion at to Sciara del Fuoco on the volcano’s northern flank, where you may be rewarded with distant firework like displays of the volcanos explosions. Head back to the boat for a good nights sleep.  </span></p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast, Lunch</p>
<p><strong>Day 6: Salina</strong></p>
<p><span>The lush landscape of Salina contrasts the lunar-like landscapes of some of the other volcanic islands. This is thanks to its natural fresh water springs, fostering the perfect environment for flora and fauna to thrive. Take a boat trip around the island and see the steep coastal cliffs rise from the sea. From the water you’ll see the islands two peaks, Monte Fossa delle Felci and Monte dei Porri, which are both extinct volcanoes and some of the highest points in the archipelago. Stop in the harbour to explore the island.</span></p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast, Lunch</p>
<p><strong>Day 7: Vulcano</strong></p>
<p><span>Today you’ll head back to the main land – stopping at Vulcano on the way.</span></p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast, Lunch</p>
<p><strong>Day 8: Catania or Palermo - UK</strong></p>
<p><span>Enjoy your final breakfast aboard the boat before being transferred back to the airport for your flight home.</span></p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/tours-multi-centres/tours-multi-centres-in-italy/sailing-the-aeolian-islands#Tour highlights">[Back to top]</a></p>
<h2><a name="Your holiday includes"></a><span class="geolocation-title">Your holiday includes</span></h2>
<ul>
<li>7 nights half board (breakfast and lunch) accommodation in a double cabin with en suite facilities</li>
<li>Shuttle transfers to and from the airport </li>
<li>Daily cleaning of the cabin, with weekly linen change</li>
<li>Welcome drink </li>
<li>Water and wine with lunch</li>
</ul>
<p><span></span><strong>Your holiday excludes:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Any extras, drinks and personal expenses</li>
<li>Any meals not included in the itinerary (Dinner onboard is available for a supplement but we recommend dining in a local restaurant on the islands)</li>
<li>Entrance tickets</li>
<li>Tourist Tax, landing &amp; port taxes (approx. €5)</li>
</ul>
<p style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/tours-multi-centres/tours-multi-centres-in-italy/sailing-the-aeolian-islands#Tour highlights">[Back to top]</a></p>
<h2><a name="Hotels"></a><span class="geolocation-title">Hotels</span></h2>
<p>Enjoy a truly unique experience and stay in a cosy cabin on board a traditional wooden Turkish Yacht called a Gulet Boat. Cabins have en-suite bathrooms and air conditioning (6 hours per day)</p>
<p><strong>Your Food:<span> </span></strong>Continental breakfast includes coffee, milk, butter, jam, bread, cookies and  cornflakes. Lunch consists of an apetiser and main course with a side dish. Water and wine is included.</p>
<p> </p>
